docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, July 16 (AP). -- Paraguay's Chaco delegates today bought tickets to return to Asuncion next Saturday on the steamer Southern Cross, after informing Chairman, White last night their government had reaffirmed its decision to withdraw from the negotiations with Bolivia.

docs.lead_paragraph: Strength in United States Government bonds, especially issues bearing the lower coupons, which are affected by the provisions of the home-loan bill, featured the bond market on the Stock Exchange yesterday. Domestic corporation bonds were moderately steady, and foreign loans, although averaging slightly lower for the day, developed several strong spots.

docs.snippet: The Commerce Department's classified statement on origin and destination of gold imported and exported during June, in which the exports exceeded those of May and rose to the largest figure of any month, on record excepting last October, indicates...
docs.lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department's classified statement on origin and destination of gold imported and exported during June, in which the exports exceeded those of May and rose to the largest figure of any month, on record excepting last October, indicates that the month's exports of $226,116,680 went to ten different countries, while the imports of $18,394,738 were received, sometimes in relatively small amounts, from thirty-two separate countries.
